<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <%- include('includes/head', { title: 'Choose Your Claim Path', nonce: nonce }) %>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.folder/shared.css" />
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.folder/claimFiling.css" />

  <body>
    <div class="page-wrapper">
      <%- include('includes/header', { nonce: nonce }) %>

      <h1>Choose Your Claim Path</h1>

      <!-- Wrap columns in a flex container -->
      <div class="claim-menu-wrapper">

        <!-- Left Column: Guidance -->
        <div class="guidance-column">
          <div id="guidanceWrapper">
            <div id="flowContainerWrapper">
              <button id="showFlowBtn">Need Guidance</button>
              <div id="flowContainer"></div>
            </div>

            <div id="guidanceRequirements" class="hidden">
              <h3>Major VA Disability Requirements</h3>
              <p>VA disability is based on the following three major requirements:</p>
              <ul>
                <li>Connection to your service – the onset of your condition must be linked to the time of active service.</li>
                <li>The condition must be chronic – continue attending your medical appointments and follow prescribed medications and treatments as directed.</li>
                <li>It must affect your ability to perform your daily duties and responsibilities.</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Right Column: Claim Options -->
        <div class="options-column">
          <div id="claimOptions" class="claim-options-wrapper">
            <!-- NEW CLAIM -->
            <div class="option" data-target="newClaim">
              ➤ New Claim
              <div id="newClaim" class="content">
                <h3>Direct Connection Claim</h3>

                <h2>Step 1</h2>
                <p>Start the intent to file</p>
                <p>Once you submit an Intent to File, you protect your effective date. From that day, you’ll have 1 year to complete your claims while still being eligible for retroactive pay</p> 
                <li><a href="https://www.va.gov/find-forms/about-form-21-0966/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Intent to File (VA Form 21-0966)</a></li>

                <h2>Step 2</h2>
                <p>FOIA (Freedom of Information Act)</p>
                <p>Request a full military record (medical records, including service treatment records, personnel file, and C-File) through filing FOIA</p>
                <p>Processing of FOIA requests to obtain your military and medical records may take several months, and in some cases up to a year, so it’s best to submit your request early.</p>
                <li><a href="https://www.va.gov/find-forms/about-form-20-10206/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"> FOIA (VA Form 20-10206)</a><//li>
                

                <h2>Step 3</h2>
                <p>Personal Statement: Describe your disability, when/how it began, and how it affects daily life and employment.</p>
                <li><a href="https://www.va.gov/find-forms/about-form-21-4138/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Personal Statement in Support of Claim (VA Form 21-4138)</a></li>
                <p>Lay Statements: Ask family, friends, or coworkers who have observed your condition to provide statements.</p>
                <li><a href="https://www.va.gov/find-forms/about-form-21-10210/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Lay Statement (VA Form 21-10210)</a></li>
                <p>Buddy Statements: If possible, ask a fellow service member to confirm in-service events, injuries, or stressors that may not appear in your records.</p>
                <li><a href="https://www.va.gov/find-forms/about-form-21-10210/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Buddy Statement (VA Form 21-10210)</a><//li>

                <h2>Step 4</h2>
                <p>Gather all medical records related to your claimed condition, including both VA and private treatment records. You can use Blue Button to download your VA records. Other ways to obtain records include submitting a FOIA request or using the service treatment records CD you may have received upon discharge.</p>
                <p>Highlight relevant events, diagnoses, and treatments. Create a separate file with highlighted pages as supporting evidence.</p>

                <h2>Step 5</h2>
                <p>Submit claim, adding all previously collected records and statements.</p>
                <li><a href="https://www.va.gov/disability/file-disability-claim-form-21-526ez/introduction" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Submit a New Claim</a></li>

                <h2>Step 6</h2>
                <p>The claims process can take several months. Be sure to keep your contact information up to date, attend all scheduled VA claim exams (C&P exams), and regularly check the status of your claim in case the VA requests additional information.</p>
              </div>
            </div>

            <!-- SUPPLEMENTAL -->
            <div class="option" data-target="supplementalClaim">
              ➤ Supplemental Claim
              <div id="supplementalClaim" class="content">
                 <p>Collect additional information that could support your claim, such as:</p>
  <ul>
  <li>New doctor visits</li>
  <li>Test results</li>
  <li>Other relevant medical documents</li>
</ul>

<ul>
  <li>Personal statement
    <ul>
      <li>
        <a href="https://www.va.gov/find-forms/about-form-21-4138/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
          Personal Statement in Support of Claim (VA Form 21-4138)
        </a>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li>Witness statements, if available
    <ul>
      <li>
        <a href="https://www.va.gov/find-forms/about-form-21-10210/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
          Lay Statement (VA Form 21-10210)
        </a>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li>Submit supplemental claim form
    <ul>
      <li>
        <a href="https://www.va.gov/find-forms/about-form-20-0995/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
          Decision Review Request: Supplemental Claim (VA Form 20-0995)
        </a>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </li>
</ul>

              </div>
            </div>

            <!-- HIGHER LEVEL REVIEW -->
            <div class="option" data-target="higherReview">
              ➤ Higher-Level Review
              <div id="higherReview" class="content">
                <p>Apply, if you disagree with a VA claim decision and want a senior reviewer to look at your claim</p>
                <p>No additional information is accepted</p>
                <p><a href="https://www.va.gov/decision-reviews/higher-level-review/request-higher-level-review-form-20-0996/start">Higher-Level Review (VA Form 20-0996)</a></p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div> <!-- closes claim-menu-wrapper -->

      <div class="spacer"></div>
      <%- include('includes/footer') %>
    </div> <!-- closes .page-wrapper -->

    <!-- Scripts -->
    <script src="/js/mobile-drawer.js" nonce="<%= nonce %>"></script>
    <script src="/js/claimFiling.js" nonce="<%= nonce %>" defer></script>
  </body>
</html>
